Description: Fragment of round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Red paint at neck. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Polyaratos. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0198.05.a.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1130)
